The paper discusses the use of physical unclonable functions (PUFs) for secure key agreement, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of transforms and quantizers to extract uniformly distributed bit sequences, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of error-correction codes to improve the reliability of the key-binding system, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the hardware implementation of the proposed approach, which falls under the category of embedded systems (cs.ET). Finally, the paper also discusses the privacy implications of the proposed approach, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
